üìÅ RCA #1: PulseStack Login Failure ‚Äì July 8, 2025

Title: RCA - PulseStack Login Failure - 2025-07-08

Summary:
End users were unable to authenticate into the PulseStack platform between 08:25‚Äì09:10 CST. Login attempts returned HTTP 500 or timeout errors.

Impact:
	‚Ä¢	100% login failure across all regions
	‚Ä¢	/auth/login API returned HTTP 500s
	‚Ä¢	Tripled support ticket volume in under 30 minutes

Root Cause:
A misconfigured ALB target group caused all auth-backend instances to be marked unhealthy. The root issue was a failed NGINX startup due to a missing TLS cert reference from a recent patch.

Resolution:
	‚Ä¢	Reverted patch on auth-backend01/02
	‚Ä¢	Revalidated NGINX startup config
	‚Ä¢	Reinstated healthy targets in the ALB

Follow-Up Actions:
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Add NGINX config lint check in CI/CD
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Enable health check alarms in CloudWatch

